188823631.text: "Moreover, PTP-PEST directly interacted with IkappaB kinase beta (IKKbeta) then inhibited IKKbeta phosphorylation at Ser (177/181) and Tyr (188/199), and subsequently suppressed IKKbeta activation and kinase activity as well as downstream NF-kappaB activation, resulting in suppression of the TLR triggered innate immune response."
